# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorPath2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "When Sarah finally caught up to the core of her unit she found Kate waiting for her."
    new "When Sarah finally caught up to the core of her unit she found Kate waiting for her."

    old "Kate was standing next to an arch that nearly rose up as high as the ceilings."
    new "Kate was standing next to an arch that nearly rose up as high as the ceilings."

    old "The entrance to the western wing of the palace, the only way in or out."
    new "The entrance to the western wing of the palace, the only way in or out."

    old "Next to the gate, three Bagrad guards were laying in a pool of blood. They didn't move, their faces a sickly grey colour."
    new "Next to the gate, three Bagrad guards were laying in a pool of blood. They didn't move, their faces a sickly grey colour."

    old "Poor bastards were guarding the entrance."
    new "Poor bastards were guarding the entrance."

    old "Brave of them to stay at their post."
    new "Brave of them to stay at their post."

    old "Brave or just stupid?"
    new "Brave or just stupid?"

    old "They threw their lives away, three of them trying hold off five-hundred of us. They didn't even hold us off for more than a second."
    new "They threw their lives away, three of them trying hold off five-hundred of us. They didn't even hold us off for more than a second."

    old "You think the asshole that owns this palace will even remember their names?"
    new "You think the asshole that owns this palace will even remember their names?"

    old "Sarah looked at their bodies."
    new "Sarah looked at their bodies."

    old "Agree with Kate"
    new "Agree with Kate"

    old "Sarah couldn't help but find herself agreeing with Kate."
    new "Sarah couldn't help but find herself agreeing with Kate."

    old "I guess you're right."
    new "I guess you're right."

    old "What a waste of a life, and whose going to remember them?"
    new "What a waste of a life, and whose going to remember them?"

    old "Not me."
    new "Not me."

    old "Kate spat on the ground near their bodies."
    new "Kate spat on the ground near their bodies."

    old "They would have killed me as gladly as I would have killed them."
    new "They would have killed me as gladly as I would have killed them."

    old "That's the real world. You're either killing or being killed. Life is just trying to stay on top for as long as you can."
    new "That's the real world. You're either killing or being killed. Life is just trying to stay on top for as long as you can."

    old "What a grim way to live."
    new "What a grim way to live."

    old "Grim, maybe. All I care about is true, and it's true."
    new "Grim, maybe. All I care about is true, and it's true."

    old "Disagree with Kate"
    new "Disagree with Kate"

    old "Sarah couldn't find herself agreeing with Kate. She was always too much of a cynic."
    new "Sarah couldn't find herself agreeing with Kate. She was always too much of a cynic."

    old "These men made a vow and they kept it, even if it meant giving up their lives."
    new "These men made a vow and they kept it, even if it meant giving up their lives."

    old "I think that's admirable."
    new "I think that's admirable."

    old "I think that's the old Sarah talking, the one that read too many books about knights and shit."
    new "I think that's the old Sarah talking, the one that read too many books about knights and shit."

    old "Sarah turned to her."
    new "Sarah turned to her."

    old "I'm still the the same Sarah."
    new "I'm still the the same Sarah."

    old "Maybe we can agree on that."
    new "Maybe we can agree on that."

    old "Sarah turned back towards the gate that lead into the western wing."
    new "Sarah turned back towards the gate that lead into the western wing."

    old "Through the gate, she could see her men rushing frantically in ever direction."
    new "Through the gate, she could see her men rushing frantically in ever direction."

    old "This wasn't a battle anymore. They were looting, and each of them was feverishly trying to get the best piece for themselves."
    new "This wasn't a battle anymore. They were looting, and each of them was feverishly trying to get the best piece for themselves."

    old "Sarah hoped they'd find more gold than women."
    new "Sarah hoped they'd find more gold than women."

    old "Shouldn't you be out there with the rest of them?"
    new "Shouldn't you be out there with the rest of them?"

    old "My men know they gotta kick back a share of what they find to me."
    new "My men know they gotta kick back a share of what they find to me."

    old "They can do the grunt work of ripping open drawers, hoping to find a necklace. Gods know I did that shit long enough."
    new "They can do the grunt work of ripping open drawers, hoping to find a necklace. Gods know I did that shit long enough."

    old "Sarah saw entire chests being dragged out onto the hallway and turned over."
    new "Sarah saw entire chests being dragged out onto the hallway and turned over."

    old "Mountains of clothes spewed forth."
    new "Mountains of clothes spewed forth."

    old "A single golden ring flew out, scattering across the floor with a loud pinging noise."
    new "A single golden ring flew out, scattering across the floor with a loud pinging noise."

    old "As one, the soldiers leapt after it, trying to secure it for themselves."
    new "As one, the soldiers leapt after it, trying to secure it for themselves."

    old "Sarah's eyes drifted back towards the mountain of clothes that had been thrown on the floor."
    new "Sarah's eyes drifted back towards the mountain of clothes that had been thrown on the floor."

    old "They dresses were made of a fine silk, a rich embroidery decorating from the waist down to the skirt line."
    new "They dresses were made of a fine silk, a rich embroidery decorating from the waist down to the skirt line."

    old "Did they know that a single one of those dresses was worth a month's wages? Probably not, she concluded."
    new "Did they know that a single one of those dresses was worth a month's wages? Probably not, she concluded."

    old "You see anything you like?"
    new "You see anything you like?"

    old "Sarah pointed towards the mountain of clothes."
    new "Sarah pointed towards the mountain of clothes."

    old "Not really my style I'm afraid."
    new "Not really my style I'm afraid."

    old "But I'd like to see you try them on."
    new "But I'd like to see you try them on."

    old "Yeah, I bet you would like that."
    new "Yeah, I bet you would like that."

    old "She turned towards Kate."
    new "She turned towards Kate."

    old "Tell me, is it just gold so far or..."
    new "Tell me, is it just gold so far or..."

    old "Sarah knew that Kate understood what she was asking."
    new "Sarah knew that Kate understood what she was asking."

    old "Most of it, but there have been a few servants that were hiding."
    new "Most of it, but there have been a few servants that were hiding."

    old "I told them to round up the children in the side room over there, keep them from seeing the worst of it."
    new "I told them to round up the children in the side room over there, keep them from seeing the worst of it."

    old "There are a few bodies in the rooms, male servants that were trying to hide."
    new "There are a few bodies in the rooms, male servants that were trying to hide."

    old "I think six or so female servants, they're...well off in that room."
    new "I think six or so female servants, they're...well off in that room."

    old "Kate pointed."
    new "Kate pointed."

    old "In the years she had worked with the mercenary company, Sarah had seen more than her share of brutality."
    new "In the years she had worked with the mercenary company, Sarah had seen more than her share of brutality."

    old "The simple truth was that, as much as she liked to call these people her brothers, they were overwhelmingly vile people."
    new "The simple truth was that, as much as she liked to call these people her brothers, they were overwhelmingly vile people."

    old "Not to her, no they adored her, but to anyone outside of the company, they showed little mercy."
    new "Not to her, no they adored her, but to anyone outside of the company, they showed little mercy."

    old "In her earlier days, Sarah had thought that she would put a stop to it, but the real world wasn't that simple."
    new "In her earlier days, Sarah had thought that she would put a stop to it, but the real world wasn't that simple."

    old "The soldiers considered captured women a part of their reward, little different than the gold they looted."
    new "The soldiers considered captured women a part of their reward, little different than the gold they looted."

    old "It horrified Sarah, if only because she could see herself so easily in those women."
    new "It horrified Sarah, if only because she could see herself so easily in those women."

    old "Had she not run away with Kate when she did, she would have been one of those women, captured and who knows what else by the tribesmen."
    new "Had she not run away with Kate when she did, she would have been one of those women, captured and who knows what else by the tribesmen."

    old "And yet she had also never been able to truly change anything."
    new "And yet she had also never been able to truly change anything."

    old "If she tried to warn the soldiers, they'd do it in secret. If she spoke out publicly, they resented her."
    new "If she tried to warn the soldiers, they'd do it in secret. If she spoke out publicly, they resented her."

    old "In the end, she also simply could not be everywhere."
    new "In the end, she also simply could not be everywhere."

    old "For every brutality she saw, there was a hundred more that happened outside of her view, outside of her command."
    new "For every brutality she saw, there was a hundred more that happened outside of her view, outside of her command."

    old "On a deeper level, Sarah also knew that she needed these men."
    new "On a deeper level, Sarah also knew that she needed these men."

    old "If she ever wanted any hope of reclaiming Rosanna, she would need these men. These monsters."
    new "If she ever wanted any hope of reclaiming Rosanna, she would need these men. These monsters."

    old "That meant bringing them over to her side. For some that was inspiring their hearts, but for many more it was simply filling their greed and urges."
    new "That meant bringing them over to her side. For some that was inspiring their hearts, but for many more it was simply filling their greed and urges."

    old "Sarah felt a tear streak past her cheek."
    new "Sarah felt a tear streak past her cheek."

    old "What kind of a leader could she ever hope to be if the road back to power was paved by this horror?"
    new "What kind of a leader could she ever hope to be if the road back to power was paved by this horror?"

    old "Or was that how the real monsters of the world, like the tribesmen, stayed in power? By hoping that good people like herself were too kind-hearted to fight back?"
    new "Or was that how the real monsters of the world, like the tribesmen, stayed in power? By hoping that good people like herself were too kind-hearted to fight back?"

    old "Was she a good person?"
    new "Was she a good person?"

    old "Sarah felt her mind race, then she forced herself to clear it."
    new "Sarah felt her mind race, then she forced herself to clear it."

    old "The battle isn't over yet. Stay focussed."
    new "The battle isn't over yet. Stay focussed."

    old "Kate, gather up some men and instruct them to gather up materials to build a barricade."
    new "Kate, gather up some men and instruct them to gather up materials to build a barricade."

    old "Yes, commander!"
    new "Yes, commander!"

    old "Kate saluted and began shouting at some of the soldiers nearby, yelling instructions."
    new "Kate saluted and began shouting at some of the soldiers nearby, yelling instructions."

    old "Sarah looked up as she walked through the gateway. The ceiling on the other end rose up far higher, making the space feel even larger."
    new "Sarah looked up as she walked through the gateway. The ceiling on the other end rose up far higher, making the space feel even larger."

    old "As she slowly explored the western wing, she tried to pay little attention to the chaos around her."
    new "As she slowly explored the western wing, she tried to pay little attention to the chaos around her."

    old "For most mercenaries, looting was an important part of survival, compensating for their otherwise limited wages."
    new "For most mercenaries, looting was an important part of survival, compensating for their otherwise limited wages."

    old "A scream rang out from one of the rooms off to her side."
    new "A scream rang out from one of the rooms off to her side."

    old "Sarah turned and watched a woman, dragged along by the hem of her shirt, a soldier pulling her violently."
    new "Sarah turned and watched a woman, dragged along by the hem of her shirt, a soldier pulling her violently."

    old "Say something."
    new "Say something."

    old "Why won't you say something?"
    new "Why won't you say something?"

    old "Sarah turned away and continued to walk down the hall of the western wing, the screams of the woman slowly fading away behind her."
    new "Sarah turned away and continued to walk down the hall of the western wing, the screams of the woman slowly fading away behind her."

    old "Was this world really as cold and indifferent as Kate believed?"
    new "Was this world really as cold and indifferent as Kate believed?"

    old "Nearly every door in the hall was either already breached or was being chopped away at by soldiers with axes."
    new "Nearly every door in the hall was either already breached or was being chopped away at by soldiers with axes."

    old "Splinters flew out, scattering across the floor."
    new "Splinters flew out, scattering across the floor."

    old "This was how an empire died. Violently."
    new "This was how an empire died. Violently."

    old "As she walked past the rooms, she could see inside of them."
    new "As she walked past the rooms, she could see inside of them."

    old "Scattered across the floors of the rooms, all the things that soldiers couldn't be bothered to loot."
    new "Scattered across the floors of the rooms, all the things that soldiers couldn't be bothered to loot."

    old "In some of the rooms, she saw the faces of the servants."
    new "In some of the rooms, she saw the faces of the servants."

    old "Their eyes hollow. Faces turned down to the floor. A broken people. A conquered people."
    new "Their eyes hollow. Faces turned down to the floor. A broken people. A conquered people."

    old "Sarah had seen it before, and it frightened her almost more than the blood did."
    new "Sarah had seen it before, and it frightened her almost more than the blood did."

    old "A kind of death of spirit. People too defeated to fight back, but too desperate for life to give up, caught in some nightmarish liminal space."
    new "A kind of death of spirit. People too defeated to fight back, but too desperate for life to give up, caught in some nightmarish liminal space."

    old "Sarah kept walking."
    new "Sarah kept walking."

    old "Each room was the same and yet different. Some degree of chaos. Some degree of sadness."
    new "Each room was the same and yet different. Some degree of chaos. Some degree of sadness."

    old "She was part of this. Her hands were stained as much as any that did the killing. Perhaps more, given her command."
    new "She was part of this. Her hands were stained as much as any that did the killing. Perhaps more, given her command."

    old "Still, she walked the hall to bear witness to what she was a part of. She felt it was the least she could do."
    new "Still, she walked the hall to bear witness to what she was a part of. She felt it was the least she could do."

    old "Finally, she reached the end of the western wing."
    new "Finally, she reached the end of the western wing."

    old "Turning back around she could see the carnage behind her had only grown as more trinkets and jewels were hauled out. More people dragged away."
    new "Turning back around she could see the carnage behind her had only grown as more trinkets and jewels were hauled out. More people dragged away."

    old "Near the far end, she could see the entrance."
    new "Near the far end, she could see the entrance."

    old "An initial barrier made out of wood was partially constructed."
    new "An initial barrier made out of wood was partially constructed."

    old "Soldiers buzzed up and away from it, slowly adding to the construct, slowly sealing up the only way in or out."
    new "Soldiers buzzed up and away from it, slowly adding to the construct, slowly sealing up the only way in or out."

    old "Sarah had done as Vaelen had asked of her, secured the western wing."
    new "Sarah had done as Vaelen had asked of her, secured the western wing."

    old "With the most immediate danger behind her, she couldn't help but go back to wondering what all this was about."
    new "With the most immediate danger behind her, she couldn't help but go back to wondering what all this was about."

    old "As far as Sarah could see, every room was richly filled, but none of it seemed particularly valuable, or at least not valuable enough to risk such a reckless attack."
    new "As far as Sarah could see, every room was richly filled, but none of it seemed particularly valuable, or at least not valuable enough to risk such a reckless attack."

    old "Sarah sat down on top of the barricades."
    new "Sarah sat down on top of the barricades."

    old "She pulled her blade from its sheath and laid it out across her lap."
    new "She pulled her blade from its sheath and laid it out across her lap."

    old "As she continued to observe the hall and the soldiers ransacking every room, she drew a whetstone across the blade."
    new "As she continued to observe the hall and the soldiers ransacking every room, she drew a whetstone across the blade."

    old "The soft grinding sound of her blade sharpening could faintly be heard amidst the chaos."
    new "The soft grinding sound of her blade sharpening could faintly be heard amidst the chaos."

    old "Several hours passed."
    new "Several hours passed."

    old "With the western wing now fully secured and barricaded, no attack from Bagrad's forces ever manifested."
    new "With the western wing now fully secured and barricaded, no attack from Bagrad's forces ever manifested."

    old "Perhaps they had dug in too deep, or perhaps the Bagrad army was stretched too thin trying to defend the city's main gate from falling."
    new "Perhaps they had dug in too deep, or perhaps the Bagrad army was stretched too thin trying to defend the city's main gate from falling."

    old "As time progressed, occasional fragments of news slipped through."
    new "As time progressed, occasional fragments of news slipped through."

    old "First the city's main gate fell."
    new "First the city's main gate fell."

    old "Then the slaughter took to the street."
    new "Then the slaughter took to the street."

    old "By now, the Mythran army and Vaelen's auxillary forces were close enough to the palace that they could be heard."
    new "By now, the Mythran army and Vaelen's auxillary forces were close enough to the palace that they could be heard."

    old "Sarah simply sat and watched."
    new "Sarah simply sat and watched."

    old "There was no reason to abandon her position."
    new "There was no reason to abandon her position."

    old "It was such, sitting and waiting, that Sarah was finally approached by one of the soldiers that worked as a messenger."
    new "It was such, sitting and waiting, that Sarah was finally approached by one of the soldiers that worked as a messenger."

    old "Soldier\" \"Commander!"
    new "Soldier\" \"Commander!"

    old "He saluted her."
    new "He saluted her."

    old "Any news?"
    new "Any news?"

    old "Soldier\" \"Yes, commander Rose. Lord Vaelen has arrived at the barricade and has requested your presence."
    new "Soldier\" \"Yes, commander Rose. Lord Vaelen has arrived at the barricade and has requested your presence."

    old "He's not a lord."
    new "He's not a lord."

    old "Soldier\" \"Excuse me?"
    new "Soldier\" \"Excuse me?"

    old "Sarah waved her hand, dismissing the matter."
    new "Sarah waved her hand, dismissing the matter."

    old "Forget it. I'll go see him. Thank you for informing me."
    new "Forget it. I'll go see him. Thank you for informing me."

    old "Sarah walked through the hallway up to the barricade."
    new "Sarah walked through the hallway up to the barricade."

    old "The chaotic looting had slowed down now that most of the items of value had been found and collected."
    new "The chaotic looting had slowed down now that most of the items of value had been found and collected."

    old "Sarah climbed up the barricade and peered over the edge."
    new "Sarah climbed up the barricade and peered over the edge."

    old "Well, if it isn't our brave leader."
    new "Well, if it isn't our brave leader."

    old "Hope you haven't come to take some of my glory?"
    new "Hope you haven't come to take some of my glory?"

    old "He smiled at her in that confident, knowing way."
    new "He smiled at her in that confident, knowing way."

    old "I wouldn't dream of it."
    new "I wouldn't dream of it."

    old "He gestured at the barricade."
    new "He gestured at the barricade."

    old "Seems like you've done alright for yourself."
    new "Seems like you've done alright for yourself."

    old "Captured and secured, just as you instructed."
    new "Captured and secured, just as you instructed."

    old "I knew I could count on you."
    new "I knew I could count on you."

    old "Vaelen looked around, studying the construction."
    new "Vaelen looked around, studying the construction."

    old "What is this I heard about a mage?"
    new "What is this I heard about a mage?"

    old "Ooh, I killed a mage. No big deal, really. You never killed a mage before?"
    new "Ooh, I killed a mage. No big deal, really. You never killed a mage before?"

    old "Vaelen laughed."
    new "Vaelen laughed."

    old "No, Sarah, as a matter of fact I never have, and I think very few people in this world can say that they have."
    new "No, Sarah, as a matter of fact I never have, and I think very few people in this world can say that they have."

    old "He paused for a moment."
    new "He paused for a moment."

    old "I am happy that my faith in you has proven to be well placed."
    new "I am happy that my faith in you has proven to be well placed."

    old "You did good work today. Not just with the mage, but also this."
    new "You did good work today. Not just with the mage, but also this."

    old "Sarah leapt down from the barricade and came up closer to Vaelen."
    new "Sarah leapt down from the barricade and came up closer to Vaelen."

    old "Well, we lost a few men today, so it's a bit hard to celebrate."
    new "Well, we lost a few men today, so it's a bit hard to celebrate."

    old "He looked at her intensely."
    new "He looked at her intensely."

    old "Good soldiers dying is always a tragedy."
    new "Good soldiers dying is always a tragedy."

    old "It's gruesome business, soldiering. But as much as we try to turn our hearts to stone, we still feel every loss."
    new "It's gruesome business, soldiering. But as much as we try to turn our hearts to stone, we still feel every loss."

    old "But maybe that's better. Reminds us that we're still human, despite everything."
    new "But maybe that's better. Reminds us that we're still human, despite everything."

    old "Sarah looked intently at Vaelen."
    new "Sarah looked intently at Vaelen."

    old "I'm surprised."
    new "I'm surprised."

    old "About what? That I have emotions?"
    new "About what? That I have emotions?"

    old "A little bit."
    new "A little bit."

    old "Look, Sarah, I don't wear mine on my sleeves, but it hurts me too."
    new "Look, Sarah, I don't wear mine on my sleeves, but it hurts me too."

    old "I have thousands of men under my command. Men that rely on me to keep them safe and employed."
    new "I have thousands of men under my command. Men that rely on me to keep them safe and employed."

    old "If I broke down at every death, I would never have been able to get to where I am today."
    new "If I broke down at every death, I would never have been able to get to where I am today."

    old "But that doesn't mean I don't care about them."
    new "But that doesn't mean I don't care about them."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes down towards the ground."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes down towards the ground."

    old "Yeah, I know. I didn't mean anything by it."
    new "Yeah, I know. I didn't mean anything by it."

    old "Of course, and I take no offense."
    new "Of course, and I take no offense."

    old "He placed a hand on her shoulder."
    new "He placed a hand on her shoulder."

    old "Just know that I'm proud of you today. When the day is over and we celebrate those that survived, you will be honoured, trust me."
    new "Just know that I'm proud of you today. When the day is over and we celebrate those that survived, you will be honoured, trust me."

    old "Thank you Vaelen."
    new "Thank you Vaelen."

    old "Sarah pointed towards the barricade behind her."
    new "Sarah pointed towards the barricade behind her."

    old "What about this?"
    new "What about this?"

    old "Keep it up."
    new "Keep it up."

    old "We want to keep the Mythrans out as much as the remnants of the Bagrad army."
    new "We want to keep the Mythrans out as much as the remnants of the Bagrad army."

    old "Unless I give you an explicit order, this stays up and nobody goes inside without my express permission, understand?"
    new "Unless I give you an explicit order, this stays up and nobody goes inside without my express permission, understand?"

    old "Sarah saluted him."
    new "Sarah saluted him."

    old "Yes sir, not a soul."
    new "Yes sir, not a soul."

    old "I wish all my commanders were as reliable as you."
    new "I wish all my commanders were as reliable as you."

    old "Wouldn't be much work left for you if everyone did their jobs as well as I do mine, right?"
    new "Wouldn't be much work left for you if everyone did their jobs as well as I do mine, right?"

    old "I suppose that's true."
    new "I suppose that's true."

    old "She saw him turn around, looking down the far end of the hallway."
    new "She saw him turn around, looking down the far end of the hallway."

    old "Anyway, Sarah, I didn't just come here to talk."
    new "Anyway, Sarah, I didn't just come here to talk."

    old "I wanted to let you know that the last of the Bagrad forces have collapsed. We're now cleaning up small pockets of resistance, but the battle is over."
    new "I wanted to let you know that the last of the Bagrad forces have collapsed. We're now cleaning up small pockets of resistance, but the battle is over."

    old "The Mythran prince has entered the city and he's drawing closer to the palace."
    new "The Mythran prince has entered the city and he's drawing closer to the palace."

    old "Once he gets here, he will demand that the Shah surrender himself and his family."
    new "Once he gets here, he will demand that the Shah surrender himself and his family."

    old "They haven't done so yet?"
    new "They haven't done so yet?"

    old "Vaelen shook his head."
    new "Vaelen shook his head."

    old "They're still barricaded up in the throne room, back in the royal quarters."
    new "They're still barricaded up in the throne room, back in the royal quarters."

    old "I came here to ask you to join me."
    new "I came here to ask you to join me."

    old "Join you?"
    new "Join you?"

    old "Yes. I want you to be there with me when the Mythran army hands over their demand for surrender."
    new "Yes. I want you to be there with me when the Mythran army hands over their demand for surrender."

    old "You think the Bagrad royal family will resist?"
    new "You think the Bagrad royal family will resist?"

    old "Their army is broken. Their guards have abandoned their posts. The city is lost."
    new "Their army is broken. Their guards have abandoned their posts. The city is lost."

    old "It's just...a tense moment."
    new "It's just...a tense moment."

    old "If not for you, I would be the only one from the Brothers of Providence. I'd like to have more friendly faces in the room. Just in case."
    new "If not for you, I would be the only one from the Brothers of Providence. I'd like to have more friendly faces in the room. Just in case."

    old "Sure, I'll come along. I'll bring a handful of soldiers too, just in case."
    new "Sure, I'll come along. I'll bring a handful of soldiers too, just in case."

    old "Excellent. We'll need to move soon, their army is going to be entering the throne room any moment."
    new "Excellent. We'll need to move soon, their army is going to be entering the throne room any moment."

    old "Sarah selected a handful of soldiers."
    new "Sarah selected a handful of soldiers."

    old "It wasn't much, especially not if the Mythrans would decide to cross them, but it would be enough to put up a short fight. Perhaps enough to run away."
    new "It wasn't much, especially not if the Mythrans would decide to cross them, but it would be enough to put up a short fight. Perhaps enough to run away."

    old "Sarah had come to learn that a lot could go wrong near the end of a contract."
    new "Sarah had come to learn that a lot could go wrong near the end of a contract."

    old "More than one lord or lady had tried to short them on their pay when the time came to pay up."
    new "More than one lord or lady had tried to short them on their pay when the time came to pay up."

    old "With her personal entourage in tow, Sarah joined up with Vaelen and together they sat off for the throne room."
    new "With her personal entourage in tow, Sarah joined up with Vaelen and together they sat off for the throne room."

